# profile.conf — the two contours, configured independently (INFO-033 п.3).
# Copy to profile.conf next to this file and edit. Shell KEY=VALUE, no spaces.

# Digest contour: daily send time (24h HH:MM). launchd fires the digest at
# exactly this time (±5 min hard criterion rides on launchd's precision).
DIGEST_TIME="09:05"

# Dialogue contour: quiet hours (night). System events (gates, E1, results,
# overdue) born inside this window are QUEUED and delivered when it ends —
# blockers first. Your own messages are acked even at night: you started the
# conversation. Window may cross midnight.
QUIET_START="23:00"
QUIET_END="08:00"

# NARRATIVE feed detail level (INFO-009/016): 1 = gates only (no beats),
# 2 = beat headlines (broad strokes), 3 = full reasoning beats.
DETAIL_LEVEL="2"

# The explicit word for risk-level HUMAN-TASK confirmations (H5). Buttons are
# never offered for those; only this word, typed, is accepted.
RISK_WORD="ПОДТВЕРЖДАЮ"

# Bot token file. PRODUCTION: point at the path the kit interview stored —
# <your Qroky workspace>/.qroky/telegram.token (question 5 of the installer).
# TEST: any file holding a test-bot token. The token itself never appears in
# any log or config — only this path does.
TOKEN_FILE="$HOME/qroky/.qroky/telegram.token"

# Telegram Bot API base — change only for the dry-run harness.
API_BASE="https://api.telegram.org"

# ---- Project router (ATOM-111, INFO-034) ------------------------------------
# One bot serves every project registered in ~/.qroky/registry (one workspace
# path per line; register.sh / unregister.sh manage it). The FIRST entry is
# the PRIMARY workspace, and ITS profile.conf — this file — is the human-level
# home: everything above (digest time, quiet hours, detail, risk word, token
# path) is read from here for the whole machine. With one registered project
# the head behaves exactly like v1.

# Per-project override — the ONLY setting a non-primary workspace's own
# profile.conf is read for: the label shown in «[проект]» event prefixes,
# /status sections, and re-ask buttons. Default: the workspace folder name.
#PROJECT_NAME="miapos"

# Human-level (this file, primary only): adds an «общий» button to the
# project re-ask, routing unaddressed thoughts to the named project's inbox.
#DEFAULT_PROJECT="miapos"

# Owner-visible language of the head (ATOM-105): en | ro | ru. The kit
# writes your question-1 answer here at deploy; absent -> Russian.
LANGUAGE="ru"
